 893:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/libs/bin_decoder/lv_bin_decoder.c ****              * Take bpp = 4 as example, alpha value of 0x0 to 0x0F should be
 894:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/libs/bin_decoder/lv_bin_decoder.c ****              * mapped to 0x00 to 0xFF. Using below equation will give us 0x00 to 0xF0
 895:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/libs/bin_decoder/lv_bin_decoder.c ****              * thus causes error. We can simply interpolate the value to fix it.
 896:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/libs/bin_decoder/lv_bin_decoder.c ****              *
 897:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/libs/bin_decoder/lv_bin_decoder.c ****              * Equation: *out = ((*in >> shift) & mask) << (8 - bpp);
 898:../../Middlewares/LVGL/GUI/lvgl/src/libs/bin_decoder/lv_bin_decoder.c ****              * Ideal: *out = ((*in >> shift) & mask) * 255 / ((1L << bpp) - 1)
